## 7. Success Metrics

### 7.1 Adoption Metrics

**Primary:**
- **Scene Tool Usage Rate:** 60% of users in Comprehensive Mode use scene development
  - Baseline: 40% in Quick Mode
  - Target: 75% by Month 3

- **Scenes Created per Story:** Average 8-12 scenes per completed story
  - Quick Mode: 5-7 scenes
  - Comprehensive Mode: 10-15 scenes

**Secondary:**
- Template usage rate: 50% of scenes use templates
- Multi-scene stories: 70% of users create 3+ scenes
- Scene completion rate: 65% of started scenes reach "drafted" status

### 7.2 Quality Metrics

**Scene Quality:**
- **Show Don't Tell Score:** Average score of 6.5+/10
  - Track improvement over time for same user
  - Measure impact of coach feedback on subsequent scenes

- **Framework Completion:** All three Movie Time sections filled
  - ACTION: 85% completion
  - EMOTION: 75% completion
  - MEANING: 70% completion

**AI Effectiveness:**
- **AI Draft Acceptance:** 60% of generated drafts used (with or without edits)
- **Edit Rate:** Users edit 40% of AI-generated content on average
- **Regeneration Rate:** <20% of drafts regenerated (indicates satisfaction)

### 7.3 Engagement Metrics

**Time Metrics:**
- **Time per Scene:** 8-12 minutes average
  - Quick Mode: 5-8 minutes
  - Comprehensive Mode: 10-15 minutes
  
- **Show Don't Tell Coach Usage:** Used on 40% of scenes
  - Application rate of suggestions: 50%

**Feature Usage:**
- Sensory detail enhancement: 35% usage
- Scene templates: 50% usage
- Preview mode: 60% usage
- Character selector: 70% usage (vs. manual entry)

### 7.4 Success Indicators

**User Satisfaction:**
- Post-scene survey: "Was this scene tool helpful?" â†’ 80%+ "Yes"
- Feature rating: 4.2+/5.0 stars
- NPS contribution: +10 points to overall app NPS

**Story Completion Impact:**
- Stories with developed scenes have 25% higher completion rate
- Export rate: 70% of stories with scenes are exported
- User retention: Scene tool users 2x more likely to return

### 7.5 Learning Metrics

**Skill Development:**
- Show Don't Tell score improvement over first 5 scenes: +2 points average
- Framework understanding: 75% of users fill all sections by scene 3
- Independent usage: 60% of users stop using templates by scene 5

**Support Reduction:**
- Help requests related to scene development: <5% of support tickets
- Tutorial completion: 70% watch Movie Time explainer
- Coaching adoption: Users request feedback more over time (sign of trust)

