### 8.1 Feature Dependencies

**Required (Must be completed first):**
- âœ… Mode Selection (Priority N/A) - Determines scene editor complexity
- âœ… Story Type Selection (Priority A) - Provides story context for AI
- âœ… Archetype Builder (Priority B) - Character data for scene context
- âœ… Structure Selector (Priority B) - Structure beats for scene linking
- ğŸ”² Basic Story State Management - Scene data must persist with story

**Integrates With:**
- ğŸ”² Visual Story Map (Priority C) - Scenes appear on timeline
- ğŸ”² Moral Conflict Framework (Priority E) - Moral stakes in emotion section
- ğŸ”² Review & Export (Priority F) - Scenes included in final output

**Enhanced By:**
- ğŸ”² Full AI Integration - Better scene generation
- ğŸ”² Supabase Real-time - Live collaboration on scenes
- ğŸ”² Version History - Track scene iterations

### 8.2 Technical Dependencies

**Backend:**
- Supabase database with scenes table schema
- Row Level Security policies configured
- Real-time subscriptions (for auto-save)
- Storage for scene drafts (optional, could use JSONB)

**AI/API:**
- Anthropic Claude API integration
- Prompt templates for scene generation
- Prompt templates for Show Don't Tell analysis
- Prompt templates for sensory detail suggestions
- Rate limiting and error handling

**Frontend:**
- React state management (Context API or Redux)
- Rich text editor component (TipTap or similar)
- Drag-and-drop library (for scene reordering)
- Markdown renderer (for preview)
- Auto-save debouncing utility

**Third-party:**
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Lucide React for icons
- Optional: Framer Motion for animations
- Optional: React Beautiful DnD for drag-drop

### 8.3 Data Dependencies

**Requires Access To:**
- Current story data object
- User's selected mode (Quick/Comprehensive)
- Story type and category
- Selected story structure and beats
- Character/archetype data
- Overall story stakes
- Story theme and goals

**Provides Data To:**
- Visual Story Map (scene data for visualization)
- Review & Export (scene content for final output)
- Story analytics (scene count, quality metrics)
- User progress tracking

