## 9. User Acceptance Criteria

### 9.1 Core Functionality

**Scene CRUD Operations:**
- [ ] User can create a new scene with single click
- [ ] Default scene title follows pattern "Scene [N]"
- [ ] User can edit scene title inline
- [ ] User can delete scene with confirmation prompt
- [ ] Scene deletion updates position numbers automatically
- [ ] User can reorder scenes via drag-and-drop
- [ ] Reordering updates position field in database
- [ ] Scene list shows all scenes in order with status

**Movie Time Framework:**
- [ ] ACTION section displays three required fields
- [ ] EMOTION section shows character selector and tone buttons
- [ ] MEANING section captures change, significance, takeaway
- [ ] All fields have helpful placeholder text
- [ ] Character count shows for limited fields
- [ ] Required fields marked with visual indicator
- [ ] Cannot generate AI draft without minimum fields filled

**Auto-save:**
- [ ] Changes save automatically after 2 seconds of inactivity
- [ ] "Saving..." indicator appears during save
- [ ] "Saved âœ“" confirmation appears on success
- [ ] User can continue working during save
- [ ] No data loss if user navigates away
- [ ] Offline changes queue and sync when online

### 9.2 AI Features

**Scene Generation:**
- [ ] "Generate Scene Draft" button disabled until minimum data entered
- [ ] Button shows loading state during generation
- [ ] Generation completes in <5 seconds
- [ ] Generated content appears in editable text area
- [ ] User can edit AI content immediately
- [ ] "Regenerate" creates new version without losing current
- [ ] Previous versions accessible (last 3)
- [ ] Error message if generation fails with retry option

**Show Don't Tell Coach:**
- [ ] Coach button available after scene content exists
- [ ] Analysis completes in <3 seconds
- [ ] Score displays as visual meter (1-10)
- [ ] Telling phrases highlighted in red
- [ ] Each phrase has suggested replacement
- [ ] Explanation provided for each suggestion
- [ ] "Apply" button inserts suggestion into scene
- [ ] Feedback panel can be dismissed and recalled
- [ ] Feedback persists with scene (shows last analysis)

**Sensory Details Enhancement:**
- [ ] "Enhance with Sensory Details" button in ACTION section
- [ ] AI generates 3-5 sensory detail suggestions
- [ ] Suggestions appear as clickable chips
- [ ] Clicking chip inserts detail into appropriate field
- [ ] User can edit inserted details immediately
- [ ] Suggestions relevant to location and action described

### 9.3 Templates

**Template Selection:**
- [ ] 10 scene templates available as cards
- [ ] Template cards show name and brief description
- [ ] Clicking template populates relevant fields
- [ ] Confirmation prompt if overwriting existing content
- [ ] User can customize all fields after applying template
- [ ] Template selection is optional (can start blank)
- [ ] "Clear Template" removes pre-filled content

### 9.4 Integration

**Structure Beat Linking:**
- [ ] Dropdown shows beats from selected story structure
- [ ] User can link scene to structure beat
- [ ] Beat name displays on scene card in list view
- [ ] Visual indicator when all structure beats have scenes
- [ ] Can change linked beat without data loss

**Character Integration:**
- [ ] Character selector pulls from Archetype Builder data
- [ ] Shows character name and archetype
- [ ] Can select multiple characters for scene
- [ ] Can add manual character text in addition to selector
- [ ] Character data available to AI for generation context

**Story Context:**
- [ ] Overall story stakes pre-populate in EMOTION stakes field
- [ ] User can customize for scene-specific stakes
- [ ] Story type and mode affect AI generation style
- [ ] Theme and goals inform MEANING suggestions

### 9.5 User Experience

**Navigation:**
- [ ] "Back to List" button returns to scene overview
- [ ] "Previous Scene" and "Next Scene" buttons work
- [ ] Scene dropdown allows jumping to any scene
- [ ] Breadcrumb trail shows current location
- [ ] URL updates with scene ID for bookmarking

**Preview:**
- [ ] "Preview" button shows formatted scene
- [ ] Preview includes title, beat, and content
- [ ] Reading time and word count displayed
- [ ] "Preview in Story" shows context (prev/current/next)
- [ ] Can navigate to adjacent scenes from preview

**Responsive Design:**
- [ ] Layout adapts to screen size
- [ ] All features accessible on tablet
- [ ] Core features work on mobile
- [ ] Touch gestures work for scene navigation
- [ ] No horizontal scrolling required

**Accessibility:**
- [ ] All fields keyboard accessible
- [ ] Tab order is logical
- [ ] Screen reader announces all actions
- [ ] Focus indicators visible
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA
- [ ] Works with keyboard only (no mouse required)

### 9.6 Mode-Specific

**Quick Mode:**
- [ ] Simplified editor with core fields only
- [ ] Templates auto-applied based on structure position
- [ ] AI generation more aggressive (less user input needed)
- [ ] Fewer customization options visible
- [ ] Faster workflow (target: 5-8 min per scene)

**Comprehensive Mode:**
- [ ] Full editor with all optional fields
- [ ] All AI assistance features enabled
- [ ] Show Don't Tell Coach prominent
- [ ] Template library fully accessible
- [ ] Multiple AI draft versions available
- [ ] No time pressure (target: 10-15 min per scene)

